    <name>
				<text>7.3.2.4 Compute a cofactor</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Consider the matrix \(A = {@matrixa@}\). Compute the cofactors of the following entries:
</p><ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>The cofactor of \(a_{22}\) is: [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</li><li>The cofactor of \(a_{23}\) is: [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the matrix \(A = {@matrixa@}.\)</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>The minor of \(a_{22}\) is the \(2\times2\) determinant \(\begin{vmatrix}a_{11} &amp; a_{13} \\ a_{31} &amp; a_{33}\end{vmatrix}=a_{11}a_{33}-a_{31}a_{13}\). In this case, the minor is: \[\begin{vmatrix}{@AA[1,1]@} &amp; {@AA[1,3]@} \\ {@AA[3,1]@}
        &amp; {@AA[3,3]@}\end{vmatrix} = {@minorA22@} = {@ta1@}\]
        <p></p>
        <p>The sign in the position of \(a_{22}\) in the array of signs is \(+\), the cofactor of \(a_{22}\) is \(A_{22}=+{@ta1@}\).</p>
    </li>
    <li>The minor of \(a_{22}\) is the \(2\times2\) determinant \(\begin{vmatrix}a_{11} &amp; a_{12} \\ a_{31} &amp; a_{32}\end{vmatrix}=a_{11}a_{32}-a_{31}a_{12}\). In this case, the minor is: \[\begin{vmatrix}{@AA[1,1]@} &amp; {@AA[1,2]@} \\ {@AA[3,1]@}
        &amp; {@AA[3,2]@}\end{vmatrix} = {@minorA23@} = {@minorA23s@}\]
        <p></p>
        <p>
            The sign in the position of \(a_{23}\) in the array of signs is \(-\), so the cofactor of \(a_{23}\) is \(A_{23}={@cofA23@}\).
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
